+Manages Tier 1 memory — frozen behavioral guardrails auto-injected
+into the system prompt every turn. This is NOT general-purpose storage.
+
+Two stores:
+  - MEMORY.md: frozen behavioral guardrails that must fire every turn.
+    Only store behavioral re-anchor rules here (corrections, preferences,
+    operating principles). Injected every turn — keep it tight.
+  - USER.md: compact behavioral directives that do not change session to
+    session. Do not write to it unnecessarily.
+
+Storage routing for reference data: write_file to $HERMES_HOME/memory/
+tree (organized by domain: finance/, life/, reference/, etc.).
